  "prompt": "What are some things new employees should know going into their first day at Universal?",
  "response": "Here are some helpful tips for new employees starting at Universal:\n\n1. Dress Code\n- Wear comfortable shoes\n- Follow the specific uniform/dress code guidelines for your department\n- Be prepared for potentially long hours of standing or walking\n\n2. Arrival and Preparation\n- Arrive early on your first day\n- Bring necessary documentation (ID, work authorization, etc.)\n- Have a positive and enthusiastic attitude\n- Be ready to learn quickly\n\n3. Park Knowledge\n- Learn about different areas and attractions\n- Familiarize yourself with park layout\n- Study basic guest service protocols\n\n4. Customer Service\n- Always be friendly and helpful\n- Know basic safety procedures\n- Learn how to handle guest interactions professionally\n\n5. Training\n- Pay close attention during orientation\n- Ask questions if something is unclear\n- Take notes and be eager to learn\n\n6. Employee Benefits\n- Understand your employee perks\n- Learn about park discounts\n- Know about potential free park admission for employees/family\n\n7. Technology and Communication\n- Learn required communication systems\n- Understand radio/communication protocols\n- Know who to contact for different situations\n\n8. Safety\n- Prioritize guest and personal safety\n- Know emergency procedures\n- Be aware of your surroundings\n\nRemember that specific details might vary depending on your specific role and department.",
